Brian,

Thanks for the note earlier this week and for taking the time to walk through the
open-enrollment window carefully. I am confirming in writing everything we
discussed on the Tuesday call so you have a single reference for your planning.

===============================================================
FERTILITY BENEFIT RIDER - PLAN CONFIRMATION
===============================================================

Plan year - Calendar 2026, renewed at 2027 open enrollment (November 2026).
Carrier - Blue Cross Blue Shield of Massachusetts.
Plan code - WBP-PPO-2026 (PPO tier, family coverage active since 2024-09).
Fertility benefit type - Progyny-adjacent rider administered through BCBS-MA.
                        Not the Progyny direct product, structured as a lifetime
                        dollar cap through the primary medical carrier.

===============================================================
LIFETIME CAP - THE LOAD-BEARING NUMBER
===============================================================

Fertility benefit lifetime cap - $25,000.00 per employee lifetime.
Applies to    - fertility diagnostics
              - monitoring visits (baseline TVUS, phlebotomy, stim monitor labs)
              - retrieval procedure and embryo culture
              - first embryo transfer
              - cryopreservation year 1
              - covered fertility medications (Gonal-F, Menopur, Ganirelix,
                trigger, Prometrium in the standard cycle 1 protocol)
Does not apply to - repeat cryopreservation years (year 2 onward, out of pocket)
                  - PGT-A when billed as elective (patient election)
                  - donor gametes (not applicable to your case)
                  - gestational carrier services (not applicable to your case)

Reuse rule - The $25,000 cap is LIFETIME, not per-cycle. Once cycle 1 exhausts the
             cap, cycle 2 is fully out of pocket at the full $18,000 to $25,000
             range Boston IVF quoted you. Please plan runway accordingly.

===============================================================
SARAH'S COVERAGE STATUS
===============================================================

Medical PPO - Sarah is on your Windbridge family-tier PPO for non-fertility
              medical care. Confirmed effective 2024-09-01 as qualified domestic
              partner. Her PT, therapy, and neurology visits are covered under the
              family tier subject to the $1,500 individual / $3,000 family deductible
              and 20% coinsurance.
Fertility   - The fertility rider is EMPLOYEE ONLY under plan design. Sarah's own
              coverage for any fertility work would need to come from her ACA
              marketplace plan, which we confirmed on the January 2026 review has
              zero fertility coverage.
              This means the $25K cap applies to procedures performed on Sarah
              only because she is the treated partner under YOUR employee coverage
              as domestic partner, not through her own ACA plan.

===============================================================
IMPORTANT PROCEDURAL NOTE
===============================================================

Please have Boston IVF submit all fertility claims under your Windbridge member ID
(WBP-M-478291), not under Sarah's ACA member ID. The claim path is only routed
correctly through your employer plan. If a claim is submitted under Sarah's ACA
membership by mistake, it will be denied and will need to be resubmitted, and
you will lose the timely-filing window if that back-and-forth runs over 90 days.

I have flagged this with Jenna Martinez at Boston IVF's billing side directly.

===============================================================
NON-FERTILITY BENEFITS SUMMARY (FOR REFERENCE)
===============================================================

401(k)                - Alight administered, current deferral 6% pre-tax, employer
                        match schedule per SPD, vesting current.
Life insurance        - 2x base salary employer-paid group term.
Short-term disability - 60% wage replacement, 90 days.
Long-term disability  - after 90 days per plan.
EAP                   - Modern Health, 8 sessions per issue per year.
Commuter benefit      - $315 monthly pre-tax transit.
HSA                   - Not offered on PPO tier. HDHP with HSA is available as
                        alternate election. I know you looked at it and elected to
                        stay PPO for Sarah's neurology and PT cadence, which is
                        the right call for your household.
FSA healthcare        - Not elected for 2026. Would net against Nurtec and
                        Prometrium copays if you elect at 2027 open enrollment.

